JOHANNESBURG – New York based non-profit organisation Media Development Investment Fund (MDIF) on Tuesday announced the acquisition of Mail & Guardian. “The restructured ownership of the South African media company will see its Chief Executive Hoosain Karjieker acquire a minority stake of the business as part of the Black Economic Empowerment (BEE) transaction,” the company said in a statement. VIDEO: Mmusi Maimane refutes Mail & Guardian lead story The NPO praised former majority shareholder Trevor Ncube who purchased a controlling interest in 2003. “He deserves enormous credit for successfully turning around a failing paper and charting a new strategy with new relevance for post-apartheid South Africa,” MDIF Deputy CEO Muhamed Nanabhay added. eNCA